The final of the EFL Carabao Cup is upon us and the showdown will air live and exclusively on Kwesé TV this Sunday 25 February. The match is scheduled to kick-off at 5.30pm local time on Kwesé Sports 1, channel 300. With reigning champions Manchester United knocked out of the competition by Bristol City in the fifth round, the faceoff will be between Manchester City and Arsenal. Manchester City had proven unstoppable in the race for four major titles this season until suffering a shock defeat to Wigan in the FA Cup on Monday. As all roads lead to Wembley for the Carabao Cup final, football fans will be looking to see if it will be Pep Guardiola’s dream team or Arsenal, who have yet to win the League Cup under the management of Arsene Wenger, that will lift the trophy. Kwesé Sports, Econet Media’s exclusive sports content platform available on the Kwesé TV network holds exclusive rights for the Carabao Cup and some of the most popular sporting leagues including; the Copa del Rey, NBA and NFL. Kwesé Sports is also an official broadcaster of the Russia 2018 FIFA World Cup. The post Carabao Cup final exclusively on Kwesé TV appeared first on BusinessDay : News you can trust. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from BusinessDay : News you can trust. Click here to read the full text on the original website.